# CLIP ChangeLog for dev-libs/opensc

*opensc-0.16.0 (15 Jun 2017)

  15 Jun 2017; Timothée Ravier <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +opensc-0.16.0.ebuild, -opensc-0.14.0.20150209-r2.ebuild:
  Update to 0.16.0 to add support for more cards (MinInt).

*opensc-0.14.0.20150209-r2 (09 Feb 2017)

  09 Feb 2017; ANSSI <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +opensc-0.14.0.20150209-r2.ebuild, -opensc-0.14.0.20150209-r1.ebuild:
  Add a patch from upstream to deal with a bug with Sagem ypsid S3 cards.

*opensc-0.14.0.20150209-r1 (26 May 2016)

  26 May 2016; Yves-Alexis Perez <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +opensc-0.14.0.20150209-r1.ebuild, -opensc-0.14.0.20150209.ebuild:
  RBump to force rebuild following libtool dependency drop.

  25 Feb 2016; ANSSI <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +opensc-0.14.0.20150209.ebuild:
  Remove useless (and annoying) libtool dependency.

  23 Feb 2015; ANSSI <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>:
  Patch to properly handle SO/UNBLOCKING PIN with IAS ECC cards.

*opensc-0.14.0.20150209 (12 Feb 2015)

  12 Feb 2015; Marion Daubignard <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +opensc-0.14.0.20150209.ebuild, -opensc-0.13.0-r4.ebuild,
  -files/opensc-0.13.0_IASECC_GEMALTO_v2.patch,
  +files/Provisioning_without_attributes_completion_at_P15_level.patch:
  Bump of opensc version to get ias-ecc smartcards support with better 
  attributes management and P11 compliance.
  Version packaged = checkout du GitHub on Feb, 9th 2015, SHA1 commit =
  3c1d8ad69557adf6aab08bc549188425c8b33a92

